Sentencas: A button solid oxide fuel cell with a La0.6Sr0.4CO0.2Fe0.8O3 cathode and a nickel-YSZ anode was tested over a range of temperatures from 650 to 800 degrees C and a range of pressures from 101 to 724 kPa.
Titulo: Effects of temperature and pressure on the performance of a solid oxide fuel cell running on steam reformate of kerosene

Sentencas: The fuel was simulated steam-reformed kerosene and the oxidant was air.
Titulo: Effects of temperature and pressure on the performance of a solid oxide fuel cell running on steam reformate of kerosene

Sentencas: The observed increases in open circuit voltages (OCVs) at elevated pressures were accurately predicted by the Nernst equation.
Titulo: Effects of temperature and pressure on the performance of a solid oxide fuel cell running on steam reformate of kerosene

Sentencas: Kinetics also increased with the pressure, although the power boost due to improved kinetics was just more than half as large as the boost due to increased OCV.
Titulo: Effects of temperature and pressure on the performance of a solid oxide fuel cell running on steam reformate of kerosene

Sentencas: The power boost increased almost linearly with the logarithm of pressure.
Titulo: Effects of temperature and pressure on the performance of a solid oxide fuel cell running on steam reformate of kerosene

Sentencas: At constant voltage the relative power boost due to increased pressure was higher at higher temperatures.
Titulo: Effects of temperature and pressure on the performance of a solid oxide fuel cell running on steam reformate of kerosene

Sentencas: At constant current the relative power boost was the same for all temperatures.
Titulo: Effects of temperature and pressure on the performance of a solid oxide fuel cell running on steam reformate of kerosene

Sentencas: When the pressure was increased from 101 to 724 kPa, the total power boost at 750 degrees C and 0.8 V was 66%.
Titulo: Effects of temperature and pressure on the performance of a solid oxide fuel cell running on steam reformate of kerosene

Sentencas: A significant decrease in electrodic losses at elevated pressures was observed by impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Effects of temperature and pressure on the performance of a solid oxide fuel cell running on steam reformate of kerosene

Sentencas: Complex impedance spectra were dominated by a combination of low frequency processes that decreased markedly with increasing pressure.
Titulo: Effects of temperature and pressure on the performance of a solid oxide fuel cell running on steam reformate of kerosene

Sentencas: A composite of high-frequency processes also decreased with pressure, but to a lesser extent.
Titulo: Effects of temperature and pressure on the performance of a solid oxide fuel cell running on steam reformate of kerosene
